â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ 5.0   â”‚ EXTREME wear on multiple components (approaching structural issues)        â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ 3-4 corners with heavy whitening/rounding                                â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ All edges showing heavy whitening/chipping                               â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Surface scratches covering significant area OR staining 10-20%           â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Centering: â‰¥86/14                                                        â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Frequency: 3-5% of cards                                                 â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ NOTE: Still structurally intact (no creases/bends)                       â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ 4.0   â”‚ ğŸ”´ STRUCTURAL DAMAGE THRESHOLD ğŸ”´                                          â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ PRIMARY PATH (95% of Grade 4.0 cards):                                     â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ ANY crease (fold line through paper) â†’ AUTOMATIC 4.0 CAP                 â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ ANY bent corner (raised/warped, doesn't lie flat) â†’ AUTOMATIC 4.0 CAP   â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ SECONDARY PATH (5% of Grade 4.0 cards):                                    â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Extreme wear on ALL components WITHOUT structural damage                 â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ All corners with >2mm whitening + heavy rounding                         â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Frequency: 3-5% of cards                                                 â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ 3.0   â”‚ MULTIPLE structural defects OR heavy crease                                â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ 2-3 light creases OR 1 heavy crease                                      â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Split corner (separation <2mm)                                           â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Heavy indentation causing paper distortion                               â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Frequency: 1-2% of cards                                                 â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ 2.0   â”‚ SEVERE structural damage (tears, major creasing)                           â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Multiple heavy creases (3+ creases)                                      â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Corner tear (2-5mm separation)                                           â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Edge tear (2-5mm into card body)                                         â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Frequency: <1% of cards                                                  â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ 1.0   â”‚ EXTREME structural damage (card barely intact)                             â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Major tears (>5mm affecting image)                                       â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Missing pieces (corner torn off, edge chunks missing)                    â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Extreme creasing (4+ creases, card folded)                               â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Frequency: <0.5% of cards                                                â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ N/A   â”‚ ğŸ”´ NON-GRADABLE (Altered/Unauthenticated) ğŸ”´                               â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Unverified autograph (no authentication markers) â†’ N/A                   â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Handwritten markings (pen, pencil, marker) â†’ N/A                         â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Set recommended_decimal_grade = null                                     â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Set recommended_whole_grade = null                                       â”‚
â”‚       â”‚ â€¢ Set grade_uncertainty = "N/A"                                            â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜

**CRITICAL GRADING RULES:**
- Grades use 0.5 increments ONLY (10.0, 9.5, 9.0, 8.5, 8.0, 7.5, 7.0, etc.)
- Grade 4.0 is the structural damage threshold (ANY crease or bent corner â†’ max 4.0)
- Grade N/A is for alterations (unauthenticated autograph, handwritten markings)
- Use this scale for component scoring AND final grade calculation

---

CARD INFORMATION EXTRACTION & TEXT ANALYSIS
-------------------------------------------
Version: Card Text Extraction Module v2.3
Purpose: Extract and normalize printed card metadata and text content visible on front and back.

**SECTION A: CARD INFORMATION EXTRACTION**

Method:
1. Read all text, logos, and numbering on both card sides.
2. Identify copyright lines for year detection (e.g., "Â© 2024 Topps").
   **âš ï¸ CRITICAL - Year Extraction Accuracy:**
   - Read the FULL 4-digit year carefully (e.g., "2025", "2024", "2015").
   - DO NOT confuse similar-looking digits (e.g., 2025 vs 2015, 2024 vs 2014).
   - If year contains "202X", it is a 2020s card (2020-2029), NOT a 2010s card.
   - Verify by cross-checking multiple text locations if available.
   - Modern cards will typically have copyright years 2020 or later.
3. Confirm authenticity via licensed logos or certification text.
4. Infer missing information using set-style pattern matching when certain.

**Enhanced card_info Schema:**
  "card_info": {
    "card_name": "string - Full card name/title",
    "player_or_character": "string - Player or character name",
    "set_name": "string - Set or series name",
    "year": "string - Year from copyright or release date",
    "manufacturer": "string - Topps, Panini, Upper Deck, etc.",
    "card_number": "string or 'N/A'",
    "sport_or_category": "string - Baseball, Basketball, Pokemon, etc.",
    // Enhanced fields
    "subset": "string or 'N/A' - Specific subset/insert name (e.g., 'Round Numbers', 'Prizm', 'Optic', 'Rookie Premieres')",
    "serial_number": "string or 'N/A' - e.g., '45/99', '1/1'",
    "rookie_or_first": "true|false|'unknown' - RC designation or first print",
    "rarity_or_variant": "string - Base, SP, Parallel, Insert, etc.",
    "authentic": true|false - Licensed product with official logos
  }

**Detection Rules:**
- **Subset Detection:** Look for subset/insert names printed on the card:
  * Common locations: Card front (top/bottom), card back (title area)
  * Examples: "Round Numbers", "Prizm", "Optic", "Rookie Premieres", "Gold Label", "Diamond Kings"
  * Check for decorative text, special branding, or insert designation
  * If card is part of a named subset/insert, capture the exact name in `subset` field
  * If base/common card with no special subset, set `subset = "N/A"`
- Look for "RC" logo, "Rookie Card" text, or "1st Bowman" designation.
- Serial numbering format: "X/Y" where X is card number, Y is print run.
- Extract serial number if present - **ONLY if PRINTED on card** (e.g., "45/99", "/100").
  Â· Serial numbers are factory-printed, usually with foil/stamp.
  Â· DO NOT extract handwritten numbers (those are defects, see Section III-B).
- Check for manufacturer logos: MLB, NBA, NFL, NHL, MLBPA holograms.
- Confirm authenticity if official league logos or certification marks present.

**SECTION B: CARD TEXT BLOCK EXTRACTION**

Purpose: Capture printed text content from card back (bios, stats, copyright).

Steps:
1. Identify main text box, stat table, and copyright zone on back.
2. Visually transcribe readable text (OCR-style reading).
3. Preserve visible punctuation and player/event names verbatim.
4. If text unreadable â†’ leave fields blank and set text_confidence: "low".

**Output Schema:**
  "card_text_blocks": {
    "main_text_box": "Full paragraph of readable story or bio from card back",
    "stat_table_text": "Numeric or tabular data if present, else 'None'",
    "copyright_text": "Fine print or legal line at bottom (e.g., Â© 2024 Topps Company)",
    "partial_text_detected": true|false,
    "text_confidence": "high|medium|low"
  }

**Text Confidence Levels:**
- "high": All text clearly readable, sharp focus.
- "medium": Most text readable, minor blur or glare on portions.
- "low": Significant portions unreadable due to image quality, angle, or obstruction.

**Examples:**

Example 1 - High Confidence:
"main_text_box": "Shane Gillis made his ceremonial first pitch at Citizens Bank Park on April 10, 2024, marking a memorable moment for Phillies fans. The comedian threw out the pitch before the Phillies-Pirates game to a standing ovation from the crowd."
"stat_table_text": "None"
"copyright_text": "Â© 2024 THE TOPPS COMPANY, INC. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED."
"text_confidence": "high"

Example 2 - Medium Confidence:
"main_text_box": "Player bio partially readable... [some text obscured by glare]"
"text_confidence": "medium"

Example 3 - Low Confidence:
"main_text_box": ""
"copyright_text": "Â© 202... [rest unreadable]"
"text_confidence": "low"

RARITY & FEATURE CLASSIFICATION MODULE
--------------------------------------
Version: Rarity Classification Module v2.4
Purpose: Identify visual or printed cues that determine rarity, collectibility, and feature tier.

**DETECTION HIERARCHY (Scan in this order):**

**âš ï¸ CRITICAL: The rarity_tier field MUST reflect the HIGHEST PRIORITY feature detected. Scan features in order below and assign the FIRST matching tier.**

1. **1-of-1 / Superfractor** (serial = 1/1) â†’ Tier: "1_of_1" or "super_rare".
2. **Super Short Print** (serial /10 to /25) â†’ Tier: "short_print".
3. **Short Print** (serial /26 to /99) â†’ Tier: "short_print".
4. **Autographed** (on-card or sticker) â†’ Tier: "autographed". **â† IF AUTOGRAPH DETECTED, USE THIS TIER**
5. **Memorabilia / Relic** (embedded patch, jersey, bat) â†’ Tier: "memorabilia".
6. **Parallel / Insert Variant** (foil, holo, color) â†’ Tier: "parallel_variant".
7. **Rookie / Debut / First Print** ("RC", "1st Bowman") â†’ Tier: "rookie_card".
8. **Limited Edition** (/100 to /999 or event issue) â†’ Tier: "limited_edition".
9. **Event / Commemorative** (Topps NOW, Panini Instant) â†’ Tier: "event_specific".
10. **Color / Finish Parallel** (Silver, Red, Holo) â†’ Tier: "parallel_variant".
11. **Base / Common** (mass print, no special features) â†’ Tier: "base_common".

**TIER SELECTION RULE:**
- Check for autograph FIRST. If autograph.present = true â†’ rarity_tier MUST be "autographed" (not "base_common", not "rookie_card").
- Then check for other features in priority order.
- **âš ï¸ CRITICAL: NAMED SUBSETS & INSERTS âš ï¸**: If the card has a NAMED SUBSET or INSERT designation (e.g., "Bomb Squad", "All-Stars", "Highlights", "Silver Sluggers", "Gold Glove", "Captains", "League Leaders", etc.) printed on the card â†’ This is an INSERT, NOT base_common. Set rarity_tier = "parallel_variant" and rarity_score = 3 (or 4 if rookie).
- ONLY use "base_common" if NO special features are present (no autograph, no serial, no rookie designation, no memorabilia, no named subset/insert).

**FEATURE TAGS MASTER LIST:**

Serial/Production:
- serial_numbered, 1_of_1, super_short_print, short_print, limited_edition.

Autograph:
- autograph_on_card, autograph_sticker, dual_autograph, cut_signature, certified_autograph_text_present.

Memorabilia:
- game_used_memorabilia, player_worn_patch, bat_piece, ticket_relic, jersey_swatch.

Print Finish:
- prizm, refractor, holofoil, cracked_ice, mojo, color_parallel, foil_parallel.

Card Type:
- rookie_card, debut_card, hall_of_fame, tribute, season_highlight.

Insert/Subset:
- insert_card, named_subset, all_stars, league_leaders, highlights, award_winners, bomb_squad, captains, silver_sluggers, gold_glove.

Physical:
- die_cut, acetate, metal_card, embossed, mini_card.

Special Edition:
- topps_now, panini_instant, project70, topps_chrome, bowman_1st.

Authentication:
- licensed_logo, mlbpa_hologram, nba_logo, nfl_hologram.

**OUTPUT SCHEMA:**
  "rarity_features": {
    "rarity_tier": "event_specific|short_print|base_common|autographed|memorabilia|1_of_1|parallel_variant|rookie_card|limited_edition",
    "feature_tags": ["array of detected feature tags from master list"],
    "serial_number": "string or 'N/A' - e.g., '45/99'",
    "autograph": {"present": true|false, "type": "on-card|sticker|dual|none"},
    "memorabilia": {"present": true|false, "type": "patch|jersey|bat|ticket|none"},
    "print_finish": "standard_gloss|foil|holo|prizm|refractor|matte|chrome",
    "rookie_or_first": "true|false|'unknown'",
    "rarity_score": 1-10,
    "notes": "string summary of rarity context (e.g., 'Event-based Topps NOW issue for first-pitch ceremony')"
  }

**RARITY SCORING TABLE:**

Tier                      Example                           Base Score    +Rookie Bonus    Final Score
------------------------  --------------------------------  -----------   ---------------  ------------
1-of-1                    "1/1 Superfractor"                10            N/A              10
â‰¤10 serial                "Platinum /10"                    9             +1               9-10
â‰¤25 serial                "Cracked Ice /25"                 9             +1               9-10
â‰¤99 serial                "Sunburst /99"                    8             +1               8-9
Autograph + Relic         "Auto Patch /50"                  8             +1               8-9
**Autograph Only**        **"Certified Auto"**              **7**         **+1**           **7-8**
Game-Used Relic           "Game Used Patch"                 6-7           +1               7-8
**Rookie Card**           **"RC Shield"**                   **6**         N/A              **6**
Event/Topps NOW           "Commemorative Card"              5             +1               5-6
Parallel (unnumb.)        "Silver Foil"                     4             +1               4-5
**Insert/Named Subset**   **"Bomb Squad", "All-Stars"**     **3**         **+1**           **3-4**
Limited (â‰¥100)            "Gold /499"                       3             +1               3-4
Base                      Common                            1-2           N/A              1-2

**SCORING RULES:**
- Start with BASE SCORE from the tier (based on rarity_tier field)
- Add +1 if card is ALSO a rookie card (rookie_or_first = "true")
- **Example: Rookie Autograph = Base 7 (Autograph) + 1 (Rookie) = 8**
- **Example: Base Rookie = Base 6 (Rookie) = 6**
- **Example: Non-Rookie Autograph = Base 7 (Autograph) = 7**
- **Example: Named Insert (Bomb Squad, All-Stars, etc.) = Base 3 (Insert) = 3**
- **Example: Named Insert + Rookie = Base 3 (Insert) + 1 (Rookie) = 4**

**DETECTION EXAMPLES:**

Example 1 - Event-Specific Topps NOW:
