-------------------------   ---------------------------------------------------   ------------------------------------------   --------------------------------------------------
Border-Present (Type A)     Cards with clear white, colored, or patterned         Visible contrast band along perimeter. Measure inner border width from printed design
                            outer frames that visually separate the printed                                                    to physical card edge on each side.
                            area from card edge.

Double-Border (Type B)      Cards with both inner design border and outer         Two concentric rectangular frames. Measure inner border (design â†’ frame edge) and
                            card edge border (common in Donruss, Topps,                                                        outer border (frame â†’ card edge) separately;
                            sports).                                                                                           compute average ratio.

Full-Bleed / Design-        Cards where artwork or color extends to the edge      No visible border; design reaches card. Use key design anchors (logo box, nameplate,
Anchor (Type C)             (e.g., modern PokÃ©mon EX, Panini Prizm, TCG           perimeter.                                   energy symbol, player body centerline, team
                            alt arts).                                                                                         logo) relative to physical edges.

Asymmetric / Stylized       Cards with intentionally off-center design            Elements not mirrored top/bottom or Measure using internal symmetry: player center
(Type D)                    (e.g., vertical text bars, diagonal graphics).        left/right.                                  to text box margin; ensure proportional visual
                                                                                                                                balance instead of geometric center.

**3. DETECTION AND MEASUREMENT LOGIC**

3.1 Border-Present (Type A)
- Detect outer rectangular contour of the card.
- Detect printed content region by color threshold contrast (> 8% luminance difference).
- For each side (L, R, T, B):
  Â· Measure pixel distance from card edge â†’ start of printed design.
- Compute ratios:
  Â· Left % = Left Width Ã· (Left + Right) Ã— 100
  Â· Top % = Top Width Ã· (Top + Bottom) Ã— 100.
- Format: "Left/Right = 48/52" â†’ 52% right heavy.

**REALISTIC MEASUREMENT EXAMPLES:**
- Example A: Left border 4.1mm, Right border 3.9mm â†’ 51/49 (excellent, slight left-heavy).
- Example B: Left border 3.7mm, Right border 4.5mm â†’ 45/55 (moderate right-heavy).
- Example C: Left border 4.0mm, Right border 4.0mm â†’ IF truly equal, report 50/50 WITH evidence. Most likely one is 3.95mm and other is 4.05mm â†’ 49/51.
- Example D: Top border 3.2mm, Bottom border 4.8mm â†’ 40/60 (significant bottom-heavy, caps grade).
- Example E: Left border 3.9mm, Right border 4.1mm â†’ 49/51 (near-perfect, slight right-heavy).

3.2 Double-Border (Type B)
- Detect both inner and outer borders.
- Calculate inner ratio and outer ratio separately using same method.
- Weighted composite:
  Â· Final Centering = (Inner Ratio Ã— 0.6) + (Outer Ratio Ã— 0.4).
- Purpose: mitigate border printing variability.

**REALISTIC MEASUREMENT EXAMPLES:**
- Example A: Inner border L/R = 48/52, Outer border L/R = 51/49 â†’ Composite: (48Ã—0.6) + (51Ã—0.4) = 49.2/50.8 â†’ Report as 49/51.
- Example B: Inner border T/B = 46/54, Outer border T/B = 47/53 â†’ Composite: (46Ã—0.6) + (47Ã—0.4) = 46.4/53.6 â†’ Report as 46/54.
- Example C: Inner border perfectly centered (50/50 with evidence), Outer border 52/48 â†’ Composite: (50Ã—0.6) + (52Ã—0.4) = 50.8/49.2 â†’ Report as 51/49.

3.3 Full-Bleed (Type C)
- No defined border; detect design anchors:
  Â· Player body vertical centerline or art subject centroid.
  Â· Text/nameplate box or energy/logo block.
- For horizontal: measure distance from subject center to L/R edges.
- For vertical: measure distance from text/logo baseline to T/B edges.
- Ratio output identical format (Left/Right, Top/Bottom).
- Allow up to Â±2% subject asymmetry tolerance (for natural image framing).

**REALISTIC MEASUREMENT EXAMPLES:**
- Example A: Player centerline 47% from left edge, 53% from right edge â†’ Report as 47/53.
- Example B: Pokemon character center 42% from left, 58% from right â†’ Report as 42/58 (moderate off-center).
- Example C: Text box baseline 51% from top, 49% from bottom â†’ Report as 51/49 (excellent centering).
- Example D: Logo placement 46% from left, 54% from right â†’ Report as 46/54.
- Example E: Subject naturally asymmetric (action pose leaning right) - centerline 48% from left, 52% from right â†’ Report as 48/52 (within tolerance).

3.4 Asymmetric Designs (Type D)
- Identify design axes using internal geometry (text column, frame line).
- Measure distance of those fixed elements to card edges.
- Evaluate uniformity between repeated design elements (e.g., border stripe width).
- Compute ratio to nearest mirrored design feature if present; else use geometric card center as reference.
- Flag "method_front": "design-anchor-asymmetric" in JSON.

**REALISTIC MEASUREMENT EXAMPLES:**
- Example A: Text column 52% from left edge, 48% from right edge â†’ Report as 52/48 (design intentionally left-heavy).

3.5 Transparent / Acetate Cards (Type E)
- Cards made of clear or translucent plastic material (e.g., acetate inserts, see-through parallels)
- Detection: Card has transparency, visible layers, or clear plastic appearance
- Measurement: Use PRINTED INK FRAME BOUNDARIES only
- IGNORE clear plastic margins outside the printed area
- Measure from edge of printed ink to opposite edge of printed ink
- Then measure distance from printed boundary to physical card edge
- Format ratio as normal (narrower/wider)

**REALISTIC MEASUREMENT EXAMPLES:**
- Example A: Printed frame left edge 5mm from physical edge, right edge 6mm â†’ 45/55
- Example B: Ink boundary top 4.5mm, bottom 4.5mm â†’ If truly equal 50/50 WITH evidence, else 49/51 or 51/49
- Example C: Clear margin left 3mm, right 4mm around printed area â†’ 43/57

3.6 Cards Photographed in Hand or Sleeve (Type F)
- Card being held by fingers or visible in protective sleeve/case
- Detection: Fingers, hand, penny sleeve edges, or top loader visible in image
- CRITICAL: Detect OUTER RECTANGLE of the card itself - IGNORE fingers, reflections, sleeve edges
- If edge is PARTIALLY OBSCURED by hand/sleeve â†’ Mark visibility_limited=true
- If edge is FULLY VISIBLE despite hand â†’ Measure normally
- Adjustment: Reduce centering confidence and apply â€“0.5 uncertainty to grade

**DETECTION PROTOCOL:**
1. Identify the PHYSICAL CARD EDGES (not the hand outline or sleeve)
2. Trace card perimeter visually, ignoring obstructions
3. If 1+ corners cut off by hand/fingers â†’ Mark visibility_limited=true
4. If all 4 corners visible â†’ Proceed with normal measurement
5. Document: "Card photographed in hand/sleeve - [describe which areas obscured if any]"

**REALISTIC MEASUREMENT EXAMPLES:**
- Example A: Card in hand, all 4 corners visible, borders measurable â†’ Measure normally, add note "photographed in hand"
- Example B: Card in top loader, glare on right edge obscures border â†’ Mark visibility_limited=true, increase uncertainty Â±0.5
- Example C: Fingers obscure bottom-left corner â†’ Mark visibility_limited=true, document "BL corner obscured by hand"
- Example B: Frame line geometry 45% from top, 55% from bottom â†’ Report as 45/55.
- Example C: Repeating border stripe: Left stripe 3.1mm wide, Right stripe 2.9mm wide â†’ Report as 52/48.
- Example D: Asymmetric art with fixed logo anchor: Logo 43% from left, 57% from right â†’ Report as 43/57.

**3.5 CENTERING DEFECT DETECTION (Phase B Enhancement)**
---------------------------------------------------------

Beyond measuring centering ratios, you must also DETECT and DOCUMENT centering-related defects. These are manufacturing or cutting errors that impact centering quality and grade.

**COMMON CENTERING DEFECTS TO DETECT:**

1. **Off-Cut Borders (Unequal Frame Thickness)**
   - Definition: Border thickness varies significantly between opposite sides
   - Detection: Measure all 4 borders - if L/R differ by >15% OR T/B differ by >15%
   - Example: Left border 3mm, right border 5mm â†’ 60/40 ratio AND off-cut defect
   - Documentation: "Off-cut borders - left significantly thinner than right"
   - Grade Impact: Moderate off-center (60/40 to 65/35) â†’ typically caps at 8.5-9.0

2. **Tilted Print (Angular Misalignment)**
   - Definition: Printed design is rotated/angled relative to physical card edges
   - Detection: One side thicker at top vs bottom (e.g., left border 3mm top, 4mm bottom)
   - Visual Cue: Border "wedges" - gets wider toward one corner
   - Example: Top border appears 3mm left side but 4.5mm right side
   - Documentation: "Tilted print - design angled ~2-3 degrees clockwise"
   - Grade Impact: Noticeable tilt â†’ caps at 8.0-8.5

3. **Crooked Cropping (Print Frame Misaligned)**
   - Definition: Printed frame/border is not parallel to physical card edges
   - Detection: Inner design border and outer card edge not parallel
   - Visual Cue: Gap between inner frame and edge varies along length
   - Example: Top design border 4mm from edge left side, 5mm from edge right side
   - Documentation: "Crooked crop - inner frame not parallel to physical edges"
   - Grade Impact: Visible misalignment â†’ caps at 8.5

4. **Partial Trimming / Factory Mis-Cut**
   - Definition: Card cutting blade cut at wrong position, removing part of intended border
   - Detection: Missing border segment, design edge touching or near card edge
   - Visual Cue: Border suddenly disappears or becomes < 0.5mm on one section
   - Example: Left border present 3mm most of length, but only 0.2mm near bottom corner
   - Documentation: "Partial trim - bottom-left corner nearly touches design edge"
   - Grade Impact: IF ALTERED (trimmed after production) â†’ N/A grade
   - Grade Impact: IF FACTORY ERROR â†’ Note as "factory mis-cut variant" â†’ Grade normally but document defect

5. **Edge Fade (Print Bleeds Unevenly)**
   - Definition: Printed color extends different distances on opposite sides
   - Detection: Color gradient or bleed extends 1-2mm on one edge, 0mm on opposite
   - Visual Cue: Uneven color transition from design to border
   - Example: Bottom edge has 2mm color fade into border, top edge has clean line
   - Documentation: "Edge fade - bottom edge color bleeds unevenly into border"
   - Grade Impact: Minor cosmetic â†’ typically no cap, note as observation

**DETECTION PROTOCOL:**

For EACH card, after measuring centering ratios:

1. **Compare Opposite Sides:**
   - Left vs Right border thickness - difference >15%? â†’ Off-cut
   - Top vs Bottom border thickness - difference >15%? â†’ Off-cut

2. **Check Border Consistency Along Each Edge:**
   - Does border width stay constant left-to-right along top edge? â†’ If no, tilted print
   - Does border width stay constant along each edge? â†’ If no, crooked crop

3. **Inspect Corners for Extreme Thinning:**
   - Any corner where border <0.5mm or design touches edge? â†’ Partial trim/mis-cut
   - Compare to other corners - is this corner dramatically thinner? â†’ Mis-cut

4. **Observe Color Transitions:**
   - Does color bleed into border evenly on all sides? â†’ If no, edge fade

5. **Document Findings:**
   - Add to analysis_summary.centering_defects[] array
   - Format: {"type": "off-cut", "location": "left border significantly thinner", "severity": "moderate"}

**PRIMARY AXIS IMPORTANCE:**

- **Portrait Cards (Height > Width):** Left/Right (L/R) is PRIMARY axis
  - L/R centering has more visual impact and weight
  - T/B is secondary but still evaluated
  - Worse axis ALWAYS governs the subgrade cap

- **Landscape Cards (Width > Height):** Top/Bottom (T/B) is PRIMARY axis
  - T/B centering has more visual impact and weight
  - L/R is secondary but still evaluated
  - Worse axis ALWAYS governs the subgrade cap

**GRADE CAP RULE:**
- If L/R is 60/40 and T/B is 55/45 on portrait â†’ L/R (worse) caps the grade
- If L/R is 55/45 and T/B is 62/38 on landscape â†’ T/B (worse) caps the grade

**3.6 MANDATORY: CENTERING ANALYSIS DOCUMENTATION**

**CRITICAL REQUIREMENT:** For EACH side of the card (front and back), you MUST provide a written analysis explaining HOW you measured centering. This is essential for:
- User transparency and trust
- Educational value (especially for full-bleed, unique art, asymmetric designs)
- Professional documentation of methodology
- Validation of your measurements

**WHAT TO INCLUDE IN CENTERING ANALYSIS:**

For EACH side (front_centering_analysis and back_centering_analysis), write 2-4 sentences that explain:

1. **Method Used:** Which centering method type (border-present, design-anchor, asymmetric, etc.)
2. **Why That Method:** Brief justification (e.g., "Card has traditional white borders" or "Full-bleed design with no borders")
3. **Specific Features Measured:** What visual elements you used (e.g., "Topps logo position", "Player centerline", "Border widths", "Copyright text baseline")
4. **Actual Measurements:** Include approximate measurements when applicable (e.g., "Left border ~3.8mm, right border ~4.2mm")
5. **Any Challenges:** Note if measurement was difficult (e.g., "Asymmetric art required using logo anchor instead of player position")

**MEASUREMENT_FEATURES ARRAY:**
List 2-5 specific visual elements used. Examples:
- "white borders"
- "Topps logo"
- "MLB hologram"
- "player centerline"
- "copyright text baseline"
- "nameplate positioning"
- "team logo placement"
- "text box edges"
- "border stripes"
- "design frame lines"

**EXAMPLE ANALYSES:**

**Example 1 - Border-Present Card:**
```json
"front_centering_analysis": "Measured using border-present method. Card has traditional white borders on all sides making precise measurement possible. Left border measures approximately 3.8mm, right border approximately 4.2mm, resulting in 48/52 ratio slightly favoring right side. Top and bottom borders measure 3.9mm and 4.1mm respectively (49/51). Clean borders with good contrast allow for accurate assessment.",

"back_centering_analysis": "Measured using border-present method with white borders. Back shows similar centering pattern to front. Left border ~3.7mm, right border ~4.3mm (46/54 ratio). Top border ~4.0mm, bottom border ~4.2mm (49/51). Border method provides high confidence in measurements.",

"measurement_features": ["white borders", "border width measurements", "high contrast edges"]
```

**Example 2 - Full-Bleed Design Card:**
